name: Round Is a Mooncake: A Book of Shapes
author: Roseanne Thong
description: Explores shapes in the context of Chinese culture as a young girl discovers various shapes in her neighborhood.

name: Dim Sum for Everyone!
author: Grace Lin
description: Introduces young readers to the delights of dim sum and the importance of family togetherness.

name: Crazy Rich Asians
description: Romantic comedy-drama about a Chinese-American professor who accompanies her boyfriend to Singapore and discovers his wealthy and eccentric family.

name: A Tale for the Time Being
author: Ruth Ozeki
description: The book intertwines the lives of Nao, a Japanese teenager, and Ruth, a writer in Canada who discovers Nao's diary. Through parallel narratives, it explores themes of time, memory, and distant connections.

name: Mulan
description: Animated film based on the Chinese legend of Hua Mulan, a young woman who disguises herself as a man to take her father's place in the army.

name: Kubo and the Two Strings
description: Stop-motion animated film about a young boy named Kubo on a quest to find a magical suit of armor.

name: Crying in H Mart
author: Michelle Zauner
description: Memoir by Michelle Zauner, the musician known as Japanese Breakfast, exploring her experiences growing up Korean American, her relationship with her mother, and coping with grief after her mother's death from cancer.

name: Kim's Convenience
description: Canadian sitcom based on the play of the same name by Ins Choi, following the Korean Canadian Kim family who run a convenience store in Toronto.

name: They Called Us Enemy
author: George Takei, Justin Eisinger, Steven Scott, Harmony Becker
description: Graphic memoir by actor and activist George Takei, co-written by Justin Eisinger and Steven Scott, with art by Harmony Becker, recounting Takei's childhood experiences as a Japanese American during World War II and his family's internment in American concentration camps.

name: Turning Red
description: Coming-of-age story about Mei Lee, a 13-year-old torn between staying her mother's dutiful daughter and embracing adolescence, who poofs into a giant red panda whenever she gets too excited.

name: Minari
description: Drama film about a Korean-American family that moves to Arkansas in search of their American Dream, facing challenges and finding resilience with the arrival of their grandmother.

name: Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings
description: Action-packed superhero film following Shang-Chi as he confronts his past and discovers his hidden powers while battling the mysterious Ten Rings organization.

name: Front Desk
author: Kelly Yang
description: Middle-grade novel about Mia Tang, a Chinese immigrant girl helping her parents manage a motel in California, navigating challenges and dreaming of a better life.

name: American Born Chinese
author: Gene Luen Yang
description: Graphic novel weaving together three interconnected stories about identity, acceptance, and the immigrant experience, confronting cultural complexities.

name: Memoirs of a Geisha
author: Arthur Golden
description: A historical novel depicting the life of a Japanese geisha before and after World War II, exploring themes of identity, love, and resilience.

name: Pachinko
author: Min Jin Lee
description: A multigenerational saga following a Korean family in Japan, spanning from the early 20th century to the present day, grappling with issues of identity, discrimination, and sacrifice.

name: The Farewell
description: A heartfelt film based on a true story about a Chinese-American woman returning to China under the guise of a fake wedding to say goodbye to her grandmother, exploring themes of family, cultural differences, and the meaning of home.
